# S04 — BACKEND_DEV Brief: Tuya Integration

role: BACKEND_DEV
sprint: S04
stack: Node.js (ESM), Express, Socket.IO, Tuya Cloud API

tasks:
  - Tuya Cloud API client (auth, device list, control)
  - REST: GET /devices/tuya, POST /devices/tuya/:id/control
  - Normalize Tuya devices to shared schema (id, type, channels, status, power)
  - Optional: Tuya Scene execution, energy monitoring endpoints
  - Socket.IO emit on Tuya device changes
  - Unified /devices endpoint aggregating eWeLink + Tuya

implementation:
  - Tuya service mirrors eWeLink service structure
  - Shared Device type/interface for both providers
  - .env for Tuya credentials (client id, secret, etc.)
  - Rate limiting and retry for Tuya API

defer-if-complex:
  - iOS App SDK bridging — research only this sprint

anti-patterns:
  - Copy-paste eWeLink logic; extract shared patterns
  - Hardcoded credentials
  - Blocking or unhandled Tuya API errors
